---

{# ── DEFINITION · real H2 carrying the plain-language definition prose. (H2: Real estate accounting, plainly.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact section--tier-guide" id="acctind-realestate-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Real estate accounting, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question quick-answer block. Questions are NON-heading
     (ai-summary__question as <dt>) — the 5 quick-answer Qs are NOT in the frozen
     heading inventory. (H2: Real estate accounting, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="acctind-realestate-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Real estate accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="acctind-realestate-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CHALLENGES · three places owners lose the numbers (grid-3 buyer-cards).
     (H2: Three places owners lose the numbers. + 3 H3s verbatim) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="acctind-realestate-challenges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why real estate books break</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three places owners lose the numbers.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Nearly every messy real estate file fails in the same three areas. Knowing which one you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ c.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ c.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT WE HANDLE · the six services (grid-3 buyer-cards).
     (H2: Real estate accounting, done by an expert. + 6 H3s verbatim) ── #}
<section class="section" id="acctind-realestate-handle">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What TechBrot handles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Real estate accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to your properties and software, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PER-PROPERTY BOOK ANATOMY · content-to-goal table (vs-scroll + vs-table,
     no collapse per T3). Real national real-estate specificity. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="acctind-realestate-anatomy">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How the books are built</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What a real-estate ledger does that a standard one can&rsquo;t.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The difference between a generalist file and a real-estate file isn&rsquo;t effort &mdash; it&rsquo;s structure. Each row below is a place property accounting diverges from ordinary bookkeeping.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">How real-estate bookkeeping differs from standard company-wide bookkeeping</caption>
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">What it tracks</th><th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">Real-estate books</th><th scope="col">Standard books</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for r in anatomy %}
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">{{ r.cap | safe }}</th>
            <td class="vs-table__us">{{ r.re | safe }}</td>
            <td>{{ r.std | safe }}</td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="prose">{{ anatomyNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTEGRATIONS · property tools reconciled with QuickBooks (checks-list).
     (H2: Connected to how you manage property.) ── #}
